<P>In a serious attempt to downsize (reduce) the dole queue, The New =
National=20
Green Labour Rhinoceros Party has decided on the following strategy. =
Every day=20
all dole applicants will be placed in a large circle, facing inwards. =
Someone is=20
arbitrarily chosen as number 1, and the rest are numbered =
counter-clockwise up=20
to N (who will be standing on 1's left). Starting from 1 and moving=20
counter-clockwise, one labour official counts off k applicants, while =
another=20
official starts from N and moves clockwise, counting m applicants. The =
two who=20
are chosen are then sent off for retraining; if both officials pick the =
same=20
person she (he) is sent off to become a politician. Each official then =
starts=20
counting again at the next available person and the process continues =
until=20
no-one is left. Note that the two victims (sorry, trainees) leave the =
ring=20
simultaneously, so it is possible for one official to count a person =
already=20
selected by the other official.=20
<P>
<H2><FONT color=3D#0070e8><A=20
name=3DSECTION0001001000000000000000>Input</A></FONT></H2>
<P>Write a program that will successively read in (in that order) the =
three=20
numbers (N, k and m; k, m &gt; 0, 0 &lt; N &lt; 20) and determine the =
order in=20
which the applicants are sent off for retraining. Each set of three =
numbers will=20
be on a separate line and the end of data will be signalled by three =
zeroes (0 0=20
0).=20
<P>
<H2><FONT color=3D#0070e8><A=20
name=3DSECTION0001002000000000000000>Output</A></FONT></H2>
<P>For each triplet, output a single line of numbers specifying the =
order in=20
which people are chosen. Each number should be in a field of 3 =
characters. For=20
pairs of numbers list the person chosen by the counter-clockwise =
official first.=20
Separate successive pairs (or singletons) by commas (but there should =
not be a=20
trailing comma).=20
<P>
